<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Hmmm...i was lucky ^_^<BR>
Only had to camp the chief for about 7 to 12 hours in 2 days before this dropped. It is now a much more common drop, due to Verant taking the bind locket(chief's uncommon/rare) out of the game, and supposedly making the idol his rare drop. Anywho, i found a ton of buyers very very quickly, and within the first 10 minutes or so, was offered 17k cash... refused it ^_^ hehe...the idol is still worth 25k+ IMO just due to how hard it is to get...i have seen a 56 druid get wrecked by the chief, and there is a high chance of agro and trainage. I eventually did trade it and my GEB's for a manastone, which is still pretty usefull IMO(I don't care what you all think if a manastone sucks or whatnot...i have one, it's rare as hell, and I like it...that's what's important to me, oh and yes i'm a necro and i can med fast as hell already w/o the stone hehe). I would not suggest camping this unless you are under 45, or if you have a good group. I was killed a couple times rather quickly by the chief alone, as he hits very fast, and maxes out for close to 90. Unless you have a healer with you, are a healer yourself, or in the case of necros, can heal yourself, then i wouldn't say that you should camp him.</font></td></tr></table>
